28/10/2002
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- UN International Police Task Force Commissioner Sven Frederiksen confirmed Friday (25 October) that 5,492 police officers from eight law enforcement agencies in BiH have been certified under conditions set by the UN mission. The certification signifies that the police officers have achieved the level of professional competence necessary to exercise police powers in accordance with democratic standards. (UNMBIH website - 27/10/02)
